This paper deals with variational autoencoders (VAEs) for text processing, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the choice of latent distribution in VAEs, which is relevant to natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper includes experiments on language modeling and document modeling, which are tasks commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) as well as natural language processing.
